{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784313625819,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"id":"prt_f71613cd9001n74wrhxFtGLFQC","messageID":"msg_f71611b95001jeplp1GcREFa2N","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","snapshot":"36f2155dcc95666b1b11ac51b100c031946f17bf","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313628365,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZSPOVXjfGhzXMoLtGsIaR5XG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--no-resource-map] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=LEVEL] [--service-tier=TIER] [--executor-timeout=SECONDS] [--iters=N] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\n8: \n9: Thin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: > **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n18: \n19: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n20: >\n21: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n22: >\n23: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n24: > 1. Run Phase 0: dispatch-context check (below)\n25: > 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n26: >    - `research_topic`\n27: >    - `spec_folder`\n28: >    - `execution_mode`\n29: >    - `maxIterations`\n30: >    - `convergenceThreshold`\n31: >    - `stop_policy` (default `convergence` unless `--stop-policy=max-iterations` is present)\n32: >    - `dry_run` (default false unless `--dry-run` is present)\n33: > 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n34: >    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n35: >    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n36: > 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n37: >\n38: > This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (dispatch-context check) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n39: \n40: ### PHASE 0: DISPATCH-CONTEXT CHECK\n41: \n42: **STATUS: ☐ CHECKED**\n43: \n44: ```\n45: This gate checks actual dispatch context, not self-reported capability -- the prior\n46: self-assessment version of this check produced a confirmed false-positive block (a\n47: capable agent judged itself \"uncertain\" on an abstract question and hard-stopped).\n48: \n49: CHECK: was this file invoked directly as /deep:research (typed by the user, or an\n50: explicit Task delegation naming this exact command) -- as opposed to another agent\n51: pasting this file's raw content into a Task-dispatch prompt as inline ad hoc\n52: instructions for a worker to follow (that worker should follow its own dispatch\n53: prompt, not re-run this command's full setup contract)?\n54: \n55: ├─ YES, or no concrete evidence of the pasted-inline case:\n56: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n57: │\n58: └─ NO, with concrete evidence this file's content was pasted inline rather than\n59:    invoked as the command itself:\n60:     │\n61:     ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n62:     │\n63:     ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n64:     │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n65:     │   │ ⛔ DIRECT INVOCATION REQUIRED                              │\n66:     │   │                                                            │\n67:     │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n68:     │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n69:     │   │                                                            │\n70:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n71:     │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n72:     │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n73:     │\n74:     └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Must be invoked directly, not pasted as inline sub-agent instructions\"\n75: \n76: Default on ambiguity: PROCEED. Do not block on an inability to introspect abstract\n77: capability (e.g. \"can I orchestrate a workflow\") -- that question is unanswerable\n78: from the inside and is what caused the original false-positive block. Block only on\n79: concrete evidence of the pasted-inline case above.\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Phase Output:**\n83: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n84: \n85: ### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n86: \n87: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n88: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n89: - **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n90: - **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n91:   - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `stop_policy`\n92:   - `dry_run` is normalized to `true` or `false`; absence means `false`\n93: \n94: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n95: \n96: > **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`).\n97: \n98: > **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n99: > `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n100: > Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n101: > Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator.\n102: \n103: ### AUTONOMOUS EXECUTION DIRECTIVE (:auto)\n104: \n105: > Read this first. It is an imperative to you, the executor — not background information.\n106: \n107: You were invoked via `opencode run --command deep/research` with the `:auto` suffix and a bound spec_folder and target in your message. The `:auto` suffix plus the bound spec_folder mean setup is ALREADY resolved. Therefore:\n108: \n109: - DO NOT emit the consolidated setup question (target/mode, research topic, Spec Folder A/B/C/D/E, execution mode, max iterations, executor). The bound spec_folder is your write authority; do not ask which spec folder should own the writes.\n110: - DO NOT halt for the repo-wide `CLAUDE.md` Gate-3 documentation gate. Under AUTONOMOUS execution with a validated prebound spec folder, Gate 3 is already satisfied by that folder (the prebound spec folder is your write authority).\n111: - PROCEED immediately: load the auto workflow YAML and dispatch the `deep-research` agent to run ONE iteration of the research loop over the bound target.\n112: - DISPATCH ONLY: you dispatch `deep-research` to run one iteration; you do NOT read, edit, patch, or run the research loop over the target yourself. The auto workflow YAML owns the loop itself — setup, dispatch-per-iteration, reducer sync, convergence checks, synthesis, and all loop-level artifact writes; the `deep-research` leaf owns only its own single-iteration artifacts — mixing your own inline work with the dispatch is a route violation.\n113: - ROUTE PROOF: dispatch through the auto workflow with its prompt pack so `deep-research` writes each iteration state record with the route-proof fields present — `target_agent: \"deep-research\"`, `resolved_route`, `agent_definition_loaded: true`, and `mode: \"research\"`. A completed run whose iteration state records omit these fields is an incomplete delegation and does not pass.\n114: \n115: Your job is to DISPATCH `deep-research` to run ONE iteration of the research loop over the bound target — NOT to run the loop yourself, and NOT to review, analyze, or summarize this contract. The auto workflow YAML owns the loop itself (setup, dispatch-per-iteration, reducer sync, convergence, synthesis, and loop-level writes). This contract is your instruction set; the research target is the bound spec_folder/target named in your message, never this document.\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n120: \n121: | Purpose | Asset |\n122: |---------|-------|\n123: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n124: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n125: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## 3. MODE ROUTING\n130: \n131: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n132: 2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--lineage-timeout-hours`, `--stop-policy`, `--dry-run`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n133: 3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n134: 4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n135: 5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n136: 6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n137: 7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n138: 8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n139: \n140: ### Lineage Timeout Flag\n141: \n142: `--lineage-timeout-hours <N>` raises the per-lineage wall-clock timeout ceiling above the default 4 hours for long, high-effort, forced-depth fan-out runs; omit it to keep the 4h default.\n143: \n144: ### Stop Policy Flag\n145: \n146: `--stop-policy <convergence|max-iterations>` selects whether convergence may stop the loop early. The default `convergence` stops at legal convergence or `config.maxIterations`, whichever comes first; `max-iterations` treats convergence as telemetry only and forces the loop to continue until `config.maxIterations`, which is useful for forced-depth runs.\n147: \n148: ### Dry-Run Flag\n149: \n150: `--dry-run` is a first-class flag on the confirm flow, not a third execution mode. It still performs real setup resolution, artifact-root resolution, focus selection, prompt rendering, and convergence reads when those steps can run without side effects.\n151: \n152: When `dry_run=true`, the confirm YAML emits `dry_run_halt` JSONL preview lines to terminal output instead of appending to the live state log, and halts before executor dispatch, persistent state mutation, reducer refresh, or child-lineage spawn. A fresh packet will stop at the first persistent state boundary; an existing packet can read current state and convergence signals, render the next prompt for preview, then stop before dispatch.\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n157: \n158: | Mode | Target |\n159: |------|----------|\n160: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n161: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n166: \n167: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n168: \n169: - Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n170: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n171: - Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n172: - Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n173: - Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n178: \n179: The selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n180: \n181: For code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.\n\n(End of file - total 181 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--no-resource-map] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=LEVEL] [--service-tier=TIER] [--executor-timeout=SECONDS] [--iters=N] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","text":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--no-resource-map] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=LEVEL] [--service-tier=TIER] [--executor-timeout=SECONDS] [--iters=N] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n> 1. Run Phase 0: dispatch-context check (below)\n> 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n>    - `research_topic`\n>    - `spec_folder`\n>    - `execution_mode`\n>    - `maxIterations`\n>    - `convergenceThreshold`\n>    - `stop_policy` (default `convergence` unless `--stop-policy=max-iterations` is present)\n>    - `dry_run` (default false unless `--dry-run` is present)\n> 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n>    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n> 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n>\n> This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (dispatch-context check) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: DISPATCH-CONTEXT CHECK\n\n**STATUS: ☐ CHECKED**\n\n```\nThis gate checks actual dispatch context, not self-reported capability -- the prior\nself-assessment version of this check produced a confirmed false-positive block (a\ncapable agent judged itself \"uncertain\" on an abstract question and hard-stopped).\n\nCHECK: was this file invoked directly as /deep:research (typed by the user, or an\nexplicit Task delegation naming this exact command) -- as opposed to another agent\npasting this file's raw content into a Task-dispatch prompt as inline ad hoc\ninstructions for a worker to follow (that worker should follow its own dispatch\nprompt, not re-run this command's full setup contract)?\n\n├─ YES, or no concrete evidence of the pasted-inline case:\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ NO, with concrete evidence this file's content was pasted inline rather than\n   invoked as the command itself:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ DIRECT INVOCATION REQUIRED                              │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Must be invoked directly, not pasted as inline sub-agent instructions\"\n\nDefault on ambiguity: PROCEED. Do not block on an inability to introspect abstract\ncapability (e.g. \"can I orchestrate a workflow\") -- that question is unanswerable\nfrom the inside and is what caused the original false-positive block. Block only on\nconcrete evidence of the pasted-inline case above.\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `stop_policy`\n  - `dry_run` is normalized to `true` or `false`; absence means `false`\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n\n> **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`).\n\n> **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n> `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n> Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n> Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator.\n\n### AUTONOMOUS EXECUTION DIRECTIVE (:auto)\n\n> Read this first. It is an imperative to you, the executor — not background information.\n\nYou were invoked via `opencode run --command deep/research` with the `:auto` suffix and a bound spec_folder and target in your message. The `:auto` suffix plus the bound spec_folder mean setup is ALREADY resolved. Therefore:\n\n- DO NOT emit the consolidated setup question (target/mode, research topic, Spec Folder A/B/C/D/E, execution mode, max iterations, executor). The bound spec_folder is your write authority; do not ask which spec folder should own the writes.\n- DO NOT halt for the repo-wide `CLAUDE.md` Gate-3 documentation gate. Under AUTONOMOUS execution with a validated prebound spec folder, Gate 3 is already satisfied by that folder (the prebound spec folder is your write authority).\n- PROCEED immediately: load the auto workflow YAML and dispatch the `deep-research` agent to run ONE iteration of the research loop over the bound target.\n- DISPATCH ONLY: you dispatch `deep-research` to run one iteration; you do NOT read, edit, patch, or run the research loop over the target yourself. The auto workflow YAML owns the loop itself — setup, dispatch-per-iteration, reducer sync, convergence checks, synthesis, and all loop-level artifact writes; the `deep-research` leaf owns only its own single-iteration artifacts — mixing your own inline work with the dispatch is a route violation.\n- ROUTE PROOF: dispatch through the auto workflow with its prompt pack so `deep-research` writes each iteration state record with the route-proof fields present — `target_agent: \"deep-research\"`, `resolved_route`, `agent_definition_loaded: true`, and `mode: \"research\"`. A completed run whose iteration state records omit these fields is an incomplete delegation and does not pass.\n\nYour job is to DISPATCH `deep-research` to run ONE iteration of the research loop over the bound target — NOT to run the loop yourself, and NOT to review, analyze, or summarize this contract. The auto workflow YAML owns the loop itself (setup, dispatch-per-iteration, reducer sync, convergence, synthesis, and loop-level writes). This contract is your instruction set; the research target is the bound spec_folder/target named in your message, never this document.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--lineage-timeout-hours`, `--stop-policy`, `--dry-run`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n\n### Lineage Timeout Flag\n\n`--lineage-timeout-hours <N>` raises the per-lineage wall-clock timeout ceiling above the default 4 hours for long, high-effort, forced-depth fan-out runs; omit it to keep the 4h default.\n\n### Stop Policy Flag\n\n`--stop-policy <convergence|max-iterations>` selects whether convergence may stop the loop early. The default `convergence` stops at legal convergence or `config.maxIterations`, whichever comes first; `max-iterations` treats convergence as telemetry only and forces the loop to continue until `config.maxIterations`, which is useful for forced-depth runs.\n\n### Dry-Run Flag\n\n`--dry-run` is a first-class flag on the confirm flow, not a third execution mode. It still performs real setup resolution, artifact-root resolution, focus selection, prompt rendering, and convergence reads when those steps can run without side effects.\n\nWhen `dry_run=true`, the confirm YAML emits `dry_run_halt` JSONL preview lines to terminal output instead of appending to the live state log, and halts before executor dispatch, persistent state mutation, reducer refresh, or child-lineage spawn. A fresh packet will stop at the first persistent state boundary; an existing packet can read current state and convergence signals, render the next prompt for preview, then stop before dispatch.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Target |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n- Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n- Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":181,"totalLines":181,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/research.md","time":{"start":1784313628349,"end":1784313628352}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09dbcc3cd73b3d50016a5a771acb9081998e7b2b1a2199b6d0"}},"id":"prt_f716140fc001G35fMl5Ux9h3XJ","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f71611b95001jeplp1GcREFa2N"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784313628778,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"id":"prt_f71614863001shMHOMk8NxqWqJ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"36f2155dcc95666b1b11ac51b100c031946f17bf","messageID":"msg_f71611b95001jeplp1GcREFa2N","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":70584,"input":23924,"output":55,"reasoning":13,"cache":{"write":0,"read":46592}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784313631577,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"id":"prt_f71615357001q2YQ46Ey12uxsz","messageID":"msg_f716149d70017KCEoYGjX8F9Pz","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","snapshot":"36f2155dcc95666b1b11ac51b100c031946f17bf","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313642441,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_espERt0iq8pv2khFi9YyoXv5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47:   convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n48: \n49: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: # CONTEXT LOADING\n51: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n52: context_loading:\n53:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n54:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n55:   mcp_integration:\n56:     tool: memory_context\n57:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n58:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n59:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n60:   behavior:\n61:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n62:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n63: \n64: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n65: # SKILL REFERENCE\n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: skill_reference:\n68:   skill: system-deep-loop\n69:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n70:   references:\n71:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n72:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n73:     state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n74:     convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n75:   templates:\n76:     config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n77:     strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n78: \n79: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n80: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n81: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82: agent_config:\n83:   agent: deep-research\n84:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n85:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n86:   model: opus\n87:   leaf_only: true\n88:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n89:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n90:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n91: \n92: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n93: # STATE FILE PATHS\n94: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: state_paths:\n96:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n97:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n98:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n99:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n100:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n101:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n102:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n103:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n104:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n105:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n106:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n107:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n108:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n109:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n110:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n111:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n112:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n113:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n114:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n115:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n116:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n117:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n118:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n119:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n120:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n121:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n122:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n123: \n124: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n125: # WORKFLOW\n126: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n127: workflow:\n128: \n129:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n130:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n131:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n132:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n133:     if_present:\n134:       bind:\n135:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n137:         artifact_subfolder: null\n138:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n139:     if_absent:\n140:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n141:       outputs:\n142:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n143:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n144:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n145:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n146: \n147:   step_fanout_spawn:\n148:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n149:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n150:     instructions: |\n151:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n152:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n153:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n154:       deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n155:       deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n156:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n157:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n158:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n159:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n160:     sub_steps:\n161:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n162:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n163:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n164:         command: |\n165:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n166:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n167:             --loop-type research \\\n168:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n169:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n170:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n171:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n172:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n173:         wait_for_completion: true\n174: \n175:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n176:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n177:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n178:   phase_init:\n179:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n180:     steps:\n181: \n182:       step_preflight_contract:\n183:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n184:         verify:\n185:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n186:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n187:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n188:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n189:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n190: \n191:       step_create_directories:\n192:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n193:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n194: \n195:       step_detect_resource_map:\n196:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n197:         inspect:\n198:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n199:         classify:\n200:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n201:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n202:         outputs:\n203:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n204:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n205: \n206:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n207:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n208:         inspect_legacy:\n209:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n210:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n211:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n212:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n213:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n214:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n215:         on_legacy_read:\n216:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n217: \n218:       step_acquire_lock:\n219:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n220:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n221:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n222:         note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n223:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n224:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n225:         on_halt:\n226:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n227:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n228:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n229:         on_cancel:\n230:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n231:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n232:         on_workflow_exit:\n233:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n234:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n235: \n236:       step_classify_session:\n237:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n238:         inspect:\n239:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n240:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n241:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n242:         classify:\n243:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n244:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n245:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n246:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n247:         outputs:\n248:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n249:         on_resume:\n250:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n251:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n252:           gate3_classification: write-path\n253:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n254:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n255:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n256:           skip_to: phase_loop\n257:         on_restart:\n258:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n259:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n260:           set:\n261:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n262:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n263:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: step_create_config\n266:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n267:         on_completed_session:\n268:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n269:           halt: true\n270:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n271:         on_invalid_state:\n272:           halt: true\n273:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n274:         on_fresh:\n275:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n276: \n277:       step_resolve_session_id:\n278:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n279:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n280:         if_present:\n281:           bind:\n282:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n283:         if_absent:\n284:           bind:\n285:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n286: \n287:       step_create_config:\n288:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n289:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n290:         populate:\n291:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n292:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n293:           minIterations: 3\n294:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n295:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n296:           antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n297:           antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n298:           stuckThreshold: 3\n299:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n300:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n301:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n302:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n303:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n304:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n305:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n306:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n307:           status: \"initialized\"\n308:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n309:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n310:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n311:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n312:           lineage.generation: 1\n313:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n314:           nextRunAt: null\n315:           remainingDelayMs: null\n316:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n317: \n318:       step_create_state_log:\n319:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n320:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n321:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n322:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n323: \n324:       step_create_strategy:\n325:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n326:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n327:         populate:\n328:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n329:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n330:           known_context: \"None\"\n331:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n332:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n333:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n334:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n335: \n336:       step_create_registry:\n337:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n338:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n339:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n340: \n341:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n342:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n343:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n344:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n345:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n346: \n347:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n348:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n349:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n350:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n351: \n352:       step_detect_spec_present:\n353:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n354:         inspect:\n355:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n356:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n357:         classify:\n358:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n359:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n360:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n361:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n362:         outputs:\n363:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n364:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n365:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n366: \n367:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n368:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n369:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n370:         branches:\n371:           no-spec:\n372:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n373:             seed_markers:\n374:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n375:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n376:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n377:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n378:             set:\n379:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n380:               validate_spec_doc: true\n381:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n382:           spec-present:\n383:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n384:             set:\n385:               validate_spec_doc: true\n386:             idempotency_check:\n387:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n388:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n389:               if_match:\n390:                 skip_append: true\n391:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:               if_no_match:\n393:                 append_only:\n394:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n395:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n396:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n397:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n398:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n399:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n400:             verify_markers:\n401:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n402:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n403:             set:\n404:               validate_spec_doc: false\n405:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n406:           conflict-detected:\n407:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n408:             halt: true\n409: \n410:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n411:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n412:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n413:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n414:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n415: \n416:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n417:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n418:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n419:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n420:         command: |\n421:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n422:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n423: \n424:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n425:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n426: \n427:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n428:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n429:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n430:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n431:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n432:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n433:           const row = {\n434:             event: 'started',\n435:             label: 'single',\n436:             at: timestamp,\n437:             duration_ms: 0,\n438:             loop_type: 'research',\n439:             sessionId,\n440:             generation,\n441:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n442:           };\n443: \n444:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n445:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n446:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n447:           });\n448:           if (appended) {\n449:             try {\n450:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n451:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n452:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n453:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n454:                 event: row.event,\n455:                 status: 'running',\n456:               });\n457:             } catch {}\n458:           }\n459:           EOF\n460:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n461:         outputs:\n462:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n463: \n464:       step_init_complete:\n465:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n466:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n467: \n468:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n469:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n470:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n471:   phase_loop:\n472:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n473:     repeat: true\n474:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n475:     steps:\n476: \n477:       step_read_state:\n478:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n479:         read:\n480:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n481:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n482:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n483:         extract:\n484:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n485:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n486:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n487:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n488:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n489:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n490:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n491:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n492:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n493:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n494:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n495:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n496:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n497:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n498:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n499:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n500:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n501:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n502:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n503:           - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n504:           - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n505:           - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n506:           - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n507:           - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n508:           - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n509:           - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n510:           - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n511:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n512:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n513:           - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n514:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n515:           - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n516:           - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n517:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n518:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n519:           - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n520:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n521:           - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n522:           - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n523: \n524:       step_run_now_check:\n525:         action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n526:         command: |\n527:           node <<'EOF'\n528:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n529: \n530:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n531:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n532:           const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n533:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n534:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n535:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n536:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n537: \n538:           function append(event) {\n539:             appendFileSync(\n540:               stateLogPath,\n541:               `${JSON.stringify({\n542:                 type: \"event\",\n543:                 mode: \"research\",\n544:                 run,\n545:                 timestamp,\n546:                 sessionId,\n547:                 generation,\n548:                 ...event,\n549:               })}\\n`,\n550:               \"utf8\",\n551:             );\n552:           }\n553: \n554:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n555:             append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n556:             if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n557:               append({\n558:                 event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n559:                 reason: \"loop_paused\",\n560:                 sentinelPath,\n561:                 pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n562:               });\n563:             } else {\n564:               const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n565:               try {\n566:                 renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n567:                 unlinkSync(claimPath);\n568:                 append({\n569:                   event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n570:                   sentinelPath,\n571:                   dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n572:                 });\n573:               } catch (error) {\n574:                 if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n575:                   throw error;\n576:                 }\n577:               }\n578:             }\n579:           }\n580:           EOF\n581:         outputs:\n582:           - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n583:           - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n584:           - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n585: \n586:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n587:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n588:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n589:         if_exists:\n590:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n591:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n592:           halt: true\n593:         if_not_exists:\n594:           proceed: true\n595: \n596:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n597:         action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n598:         if_min_iterations_missing:\n599:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n600:           log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n601:         if_min_iterations_clamped:\n602:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n603:           log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n604:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n605:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n606:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n607: \n608:       step_graph_convergence:\n609:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n610:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n611:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n612:         outputs:\n613:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n614:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n615:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n616:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n617:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n618:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n619:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n620: \n621:       step_check_convergence:\n622:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n623:         algorithm: |\n624:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n625:           2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n626:           3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n627:           4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n628:           5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n629:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n630:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n631:                signals = []\n632:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n633:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n634:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n635:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n636:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n637:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n638:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n639:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n640:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n641:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n642:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n643:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n644:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n645:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n646:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n647:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n648:                  stop_blocked = true\n649:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n650:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n651:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n652:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n653:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n654:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n655:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n656:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n657:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n658:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n659:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n660:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n661:                  stop_blocked = false\n662:           6. else: CONTINUE\n663:           7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n664:                decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n665:                reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n666:                min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n667:                min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n668:           8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n669:                min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n670:           9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n671:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n672:                if not guardResult.passed:\n673:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n674:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n675:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n676:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n677:         outputs:\n678:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n679:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n680:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n681:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n682:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n683:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n684:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n685:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n686:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n687:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n688:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n689:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n690:           - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n691:           - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n692: \n693:       step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n694:         action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n695:         if_pass:\n696:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n697:           log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n698: \n699:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n701:         if_blocked:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n704:           set:\n705:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n706:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n707:             stop_blocked: false\n708: \n709:       step_handle_convergence:\n710:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n711:         if_stop:\n712:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n713:           if_divergent_eligible:\n714:             eligibility_contract:\n715:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n716:               eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n717:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n718:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n719:             steps:\n720:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n721:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n722:                 command: |\n723:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n724:                   import {\n725:                     buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-725. Use offset=726 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n  convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: system-deep-loop\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n          antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n          - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n          - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n          - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n          - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n          - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n          - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_run_now_check:\n        action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function append(event) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n                ...event,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n            append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n            if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n              append({\n                event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n                reason: \"loop_paused\",\n                sentinelPath,\n                pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n              });\n            } else {\n              const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n              try {\n                renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n                unlinkSync(claimPath);\n                append({\n                  event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n                  sentinelPath,\n                  dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n                });\n              } catch (error) {\n                if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n                  throw error;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n          - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n          - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n        if_min_iterations_missing:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n        if_min_iterations_clamped:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          6. else: CONTINUE\n          7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n               decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n               reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n               min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n          8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n          9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n\n      step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n        if_pass:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":725,"totalLines":726,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784313642434,"end":1784313642439}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d5689de285fbdb2016a5a772a472481919e1c56113215277f"}},"id":"prt_f71617d5d001B0IRU1y7GX1oqI","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f716149d70017KCEoYGjX8F9Pz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313642451,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EFGGU3wz8TuxETUPdQG6WX9O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: This workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n8: \n9: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n10: \n11: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n12: \n13: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n14: \n15: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n16: \n17: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n18: \n19: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n20: \n21: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n22: \n23: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n24: \n25: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n26: \n27: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n28: \n29: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n30: \n31: ```yaml\n32: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n33:   research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n34:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n35:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n36:   maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n37:   convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n38:   convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n39:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n40:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n41:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n42:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n43:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n44:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n45:   resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n46: ```\n47: \n48: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n49: \n50: ### Default Resolution Table\n51: \n52: | Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n53: | -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n54: | `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n55: | `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n56: | `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n57: | `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n58: | `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n59: | `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n60: | `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n61: | `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n62: | `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n63: | `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n64: | `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n65: | `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n66: | `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n67: | `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n68: | `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n69: \n70: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n71: \n72: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n73: \n74: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n75: \n76: ```\n77: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n78: \n79: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n80:    |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n81:    |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n82:    +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n83: \n84: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n85:    |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n86:    |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n87:    +-- Empty -> include Q0\n88: \n89: 3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n90:    |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n91:    |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n92:    |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n93:    |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n94:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n95:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n96:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n97:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n98:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n99:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n100:    |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n101:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n102:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n103:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n104:    |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n105:    |\n106:    |   Fan-out default policy:\n107:    |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n108:    |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n109:    |\n110:    +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n111: \n112:    Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n113:    - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n114:    - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n115: \n116:    Parsing to config mapping:\n117:    - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n118:    - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n119:    - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n120:    - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n121:    - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n122:    - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n123:    - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n124: \n125:    Validation hook:\n126:    - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n127:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n128: \n129: 4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n130:    $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n131: \n132: 5. Search for prior work (background):\n133:    - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n134:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n135: \n136: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n137:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n138:    - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n139: \n140:    Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n141: \n142:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n143:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n144:      B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n145:      C) Update related [if match found]\n146:      D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n147: \n148:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n149:      A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n150:      B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n151: \n152:    Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n153:      Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n154: \n155:    Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n156:      A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n157:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n158:      C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n159: \n160:    Reply format examples:\n161:    - `\"A, A\"`\n162:    - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n163:    - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n164:    - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n165: \n166: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n167: \n168: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n169:    - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n170:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n171:    - spec_path = [derived path]\n172:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n173:    - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n174:    - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n175:    - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n176:     - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n177: \n178: 9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n179: \n180: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n181: \n182: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n183: NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n184: NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n185: ```\n186: \n187: **Phase Output:**\n188: - `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n189: - `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n190: \n191: ## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n192: \n193: ### Deep Research\n194: \n195: Conduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n196: \n197: For code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n198: \n199: ### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n200: \n201: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n202: \n203: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n204: \n205: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n206: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n207: - `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n208: \n209: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n210: \n211: ```yaml\n212: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n213: purpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\n214: action: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\n215: operating_mode:\n216:   workflow: iterative_loop\n217:   compliance: MANDATORY\n218:   execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n219:   validation: convergence_detection\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ### Purpose\n223: \n224: Run an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n225: \n226: ### Contract\n227: \n228: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n229: **Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n230: \n231: ### Workflow Overview\n232: \n233: | Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n234: |-------|------|---------|---------|\n235: | Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n236: | Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n237: | Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n238: | Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n239: \n240: ### Execution Modes\n241: \n242: | Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n243: |------|-----------|----------|\n244: | `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n245: | `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n246: | (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n247: \n248: ### Memory Integration Before Starting\n249: \n250: - `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n251: - Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n252: \n253: ### Code Context Bootstrap\n254: \n255: - Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n256: - Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n257: - Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n258: \n259: ## 3. Results Display\n260: \n261: ### Output Formats\n262: \n263: **Success:**\n264: ```\n265: Deep research complete.\n266: Iterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\n267: Artifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\n268: Ready for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\n269: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n270: ```\n271: \n272: **Failure:**\n273: ```\n274: Error: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\n275: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Memory Integration After Completing\n279: \n280: - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n281: - Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n282: \n283: ### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n284: \n285: `ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n286: \n287: ### Error Handling\n288: \n289: | Error | Action |\n290: |-------|--------|\n291: | Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n292: | State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n293: | 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n294: | Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n295: \n296: ## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n297: \n298: ### Skill Reference\n299: \n300: Full protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n301: \n302: Key references:\n303: - Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\n304: - Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`\n305: - State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md`\n306: - Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n307: - Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md`\n308: \n309: For code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n310: \n311: ### Examples\n312: \n313: ```\n314: # Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n315: /deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n316: /deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n317: /deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n318: \n319: # Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n320: /deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n321:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n322:   --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n323:   --concurrency=2\n324: \n325: # Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n326: /deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n327:   --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n328:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n329:   --concurrency=3\n330: \n331: # Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n332: /deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n333:   --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n334:   --concurrency=4\n335: ```\n336: \n337: > **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n338: \n339: ### Next Steps\n340: \n341: > **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n342: \n343: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n344: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n345: | Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n346: | Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n347: | Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n348: | Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n349: \n350: ### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n351: \n352: - Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n353: - Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n354: - Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n355: - Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n356: - Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n357: - Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n358: - Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n359: - Does NOT proceed to implementation\n360: \n361: ### Command Chain\n362: \n363: **Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n364: **Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n365: \n366: ### Offline Optimization\n367: \n368: Convergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n369: \n370: **Key constraints:**\n371: - Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n372: - Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n373: - Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n374: \n375: **References:**\n376: - Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n377: - Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n378: - Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n\n(End of file - total 378 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt","text":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n  convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n  convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n  executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n  executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n  executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n  executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n  executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n  executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n  resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n| -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n| `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n| `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n| `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n| `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n| `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n| `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n| `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n\n**Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n   |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n   |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n   +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n   |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n   |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   +-- Empty -> include Q0\n\n3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n   |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n   |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n   |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n   |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n   |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n   |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n   |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n   |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n   |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n   |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n   |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n   |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n   |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n   |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n   |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n   |\n   |   Fan-out default policy:\n   |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n   |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n   |\n   +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n\n   Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n   - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n   - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n\n   Parsing to config mapping:\n   - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n   - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n   - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n   - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n   - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n   - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n   - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n\n   Validation hook:\n   - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n   - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n   $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n\n5. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n   - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n   - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n\n   Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n     B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n     C) Update related [if match found]\n     D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n     B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n\n   Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n     Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n\n   Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n     A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n     B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n     C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n\n   Reply format examples:\n   - `\"A, A\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n   - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n   - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n   - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n   - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n    - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n\n9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\nDO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\nNEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\nNEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n- `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n\n## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n\n### Deep Research\n\nConduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\naction: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n  validation: convergence_detection\n```\n\n### Purpose\n\nRun an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n\n### Contract\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n**Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n\n### Workflow Overview\n\n| Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n|-------|------|---------|---------|\n| Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n| Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n| Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n| Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n\n### Execution Modes\n\n| Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n|------|-----------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n| `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n| (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n\n### Memory Integration Before Starting\n\n- `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n- Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n\n### Code Context Bootstrap\n\n- Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n- Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n- Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Output Formats\n\n**Success:**\n```\nDeep research complete.\nIterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\nArtifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\nReady for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n**Failure:**\n```\nError: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Memory Integration After Completing\n\n- `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n- Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n\n### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n\n`ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Error | Action |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n| State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n\n## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n\n### Skill Reference\n\nFull protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n\nKey references:\n- Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\n- Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`\n- State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md`\n- Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n- Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md`\n\nFor code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n# Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n/deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n/deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n/deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n\n# Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n/deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n  --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n  --concurrency=2\n\n# Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n/deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n  --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n  --concurrency=3\n\n# Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n/deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n  --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n  --concurrency=4\n```\n\n> **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n\n### Next Steps\n\n> **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n| Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n| Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n| Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n\n### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n\n- Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n- Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n- Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n- Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n- Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n- Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n- Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n- Does NOT proceed to implementation\n\n### Command Chain\n\n**Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n\n### Offline Optimization\n\nConvergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n\n**Key constraints:**\n- Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n- Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n- Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n\n**References:**\n- Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n- Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n- Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":378,"totalLines":378,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt","time":{"start":1784313642446,"end":1784313642449}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d5689de285fbdb2016a5a772a4740819193142d7ded3fab99"}},"id":"prt_f71617dc3001HRVm4OtP251fOn","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f716149d70017KCEoYGjX8F9Pz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313642496,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UPBY9cNSj1jVJHwY12cq2iQl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\"\n3: description: \"Deep research into whether a parent hub's routerPolicy.defaultMode should point at a child mode at all, or default to null (defer to the parent to disambiguate/detect). Evaluates each of the five auto-defaulting hubs for whether its default is the genuine dominant case or a presumption, and proposes a principled fleet policy encoded in the create-skill canon + route-gold benchmark.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"default mode policy research\"\n6:   - \"should hubs default to null\"\n7:   - \"parent hub defaultMode design\"\n8:   - \"defer to parent vs default to child\"\n9: importance_tier: \"important\"\n10: contextType: \"research\"\n11: ---\n12: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n13: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n14: \n15: # Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n20: \n21: A parent hub is a pure router: its `SKILL.md` never handles a request itself, it only dispatches to a child mode (or defers). `routerPolicy.defaultMode` is the hub's documented fallback when the request scores weakly. Today five hubs point `defaultMode` at a specific child (`sk-prompt`→`prompt-improve`, `cli-external-orchestration`→`cli-opencode`, `system-deep-loop`→`research`, `mcp-tooling`→`mcp-chrome-devtools`, `sk-design`→`interface`) while two use `null` (`sk-doc` defers to disambiguation; `sk-code` resolves its mode by surface detection). The open question: is \"default to a child\" a sound default, or a presumption that silently commits to a possibly-wrong mode — and should some or all of the five flip to `null`?\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n26: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n27: \n28: ### Problem Statement\n29: \n30: `defaultMode = <child>` auto-commits the hub to one mode when nothing specific fires. That is good UX when one child is overwhelmingly the common case (asking would be annoying), but a latent failure when the request was actually about a different mode — the hub silently mis-routes instead of deferring. `defaultMode = null` avoids the mis-route (the parent disambiguates or detects) at the cost of more clarification prompts. There is no articulated fleet policy for which hubs should do which, and the choice is currently ad hoc.\n31: \n32: ### Purpose\n33: \n34: Determine the principled policy for `defaultMode` per tier and per hub, and how to encode it so new skills inherit the right default rather than copying a neighbour's.\n35: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: <!-- ANCHOR:research-context -->\n40: ## 3. RESEARCH CONTEXT\n41: \n42: ### The core question\n43: \n44: Should a parent hub's `routerPolicy.defaultMode` point at a child mode, or should it be `null` (defer to the parent's own `SKILL.md` to disambiguate or detect)? When is each correct?\n45: \n46: ### What to investigate (each iteration should advance these)\n47: \n48: 1. **Semantics.** Is \"default to a child\" coherent given the parent is a pure router with no mode of its own? What does the deterministic router-replay actually do when nothing scores and `defaultMode` is set vs `null` (route to the default child, emit nothing, or defer)? Confirm against `router-replay.cjs` behaviour, not assumption.\n49: 2. **Per-hub verdict.** For each of the five auto-defaulting hubs, is the named default the genuine dominant (~80%) case for a request that already routed to that skill, or a presumption? Evidence: the hub's own modes, its playbook scenarios, and what a mis-default would cost.\n50:    - `sk-prompt` → `prompt-improve` (vs the niche `prompt-models`)\n51:    - `cli-external-orchestration` → `cli-opencode` (vs `cli-claude-code`, `cli-codex`)\n52:    - `system-deep-loop` → `research` (vs review, ai-council, improvement lanes)\n53:    - `mcp-tooling` → `mcp-chrome-devtools` (vs 5 other unrelated transports)\n54:    - `sk-design` → `interface` (vs foundations, motion, audit, md-generator)\n55: 3. **The two null models.** `sk-doc` (keyword-routed, no sensible default → defer) vs `sk-code` (detection-routed → no keyword default). Are these the reference patterns the five should be measured against?\n56: 4. **Interaction with the route-gold gate.** Under `sameSet` intent matching, does a `defaultMode` fallback ever emit a mode that fails or masks a route-gold scenario? Should the benchmark assert defer-vs-default behaviour explicitly (a scenario whose gold is \"defer / disambiguate\")?\n57: 5. **Encoding.** How should the chosen policy live in the `create-skill` canon (the `parent_skill_hub_router_template.json` + schema doc) so a new hub picks `defaultMode` deliberately rather than by imitation? What decision rule distinguishes \"default to the dominant child\" from \"null / defer\"?\n58: \n59: ### Constraints / ground truth\n60: \n61: - The parent `SKILL.md` is a pure router; there is no \"parent mode.\" Do not propose a default that is the parent itself.\n62: - `AMBIGUITY_DELTA` is a hard-coded constant (1) in the benchmark replay; `routerPolicy.ambiguityDelta` in JSON is inert. Reason about defaulting within that scoring model.\n63: - Recommendations that change a shipped `defaultMode` are behaviour changes to live routing — treat each as a proposal with a stated tradeoff (fewer wrong auto-picks vs more disambiguation prompts), not an auto-applied fix.\n64: \n65: ### Deliverable\n66: \n67: `research/research.md` with: a per-hub verdict table (keep default / flip to null, with the dominant-case evidence and the mis-default cost), the principled decision rule, the benchmark implication (should defer be a gold outcome), and the exact `create-skill` canon change to encode it.\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:research-context -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n73: ## 4. SCOPE\n74: \n75: ### In Scope\n76: - The `defaultMode` design question across the 7 parent hubs (5 default-to-child, 2 null).\n77: - The decision rule + its encoding in the create-skill canon and the route-gold benchmark.\n78: \n79: ### Out of Scope\n80: - Actually flipping any shipped `defaultMode` (that is a follow-on decision per hub).\n81: - Layer-0 advisor (skill selection) — this is about Layer-1 mode selection only.\n82: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: <!-- ANCHOR:divergent-agenda -->\n87: ## 5. DIVERGENT EXPLORATION AGENDA (Run 2 — 20 iterations, non-converge)\n88: \n89: Run 1 (4 iterations, in `run1-archive/`) reached a clear answer: keep sk-prompt, flip 4 to null; a null hub's fallback should load the routing helper (`smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`), not a child or filler. Run 2 must NOT re-derive this — it must **diverge, expand, and stress-test**. Each iteration should open NEW territory. Do not converge; treat any \"we already know this\" as a signal to push into an unexplored angle. Candidate divergent threads (extend beyond these):\n90: \n91: 1. **The fallback-resource rule, stress-tested.** Does loading the mode-map actually help a live model route better, or just add tokens? Is there a case where a child hint beats the mode-map? What is the ideal *shape* of the routing-helper resource (full registry vs a compressed disambiguation card)?\n92: 2. **Layer-0 ↔ Layer-1 interaction.** How does the advisor's skill selection interact with a hub that defers? Does a null hub push disambiguation cost up to Layer 0? Should the advisor pre-resolve more, so hubs never hit zero-signal?\n93: 3. **Live-mode reality.** On a null hub, does a real model presented with the mode-map disambiguate cleanly, or freeze / pick arbitrarily? Design the experiment.\n94: 4. **Migration & rollback.** Safe ordering of the 4 flips; regression surface; how to detect a bad flip; can the flips be shipped behind a benchmark gate?\n95: 5. **The third archetype, fully specified.** Exact schema, validator rules, and the `defaultConfigured` rename ripple across replay, gold, dashboards, docs.\n96: 6. **Cross-hub generalization.** Should ALL hubs converge on one archetype? When is detection-routed (sk-code) the better answer than defer-routed? Could sk-design be detection-routed?\n97: 7. **Second-order effects.** Does removing defaults measurably raise disambiguation friction? What NEW anti-patterns could null + mode-map introduce (e.g. mode-map bloat, stale registries, over-deferring)?\n98: 8. **Multi-dominant hubs & bundling.** What if a hub genuinely has 2 co-equal common modes? Ordered-bundle vs defer vs a ranked mode-map.\n99: 9. **Edge cases & failure modes.** Empty mode-map, single-mode hubs, a mode-registry that drifts from hub-router, a hub whose \"default\" is contextual (cli's runtime-dependence — generalize it).\n100: 10. **The catch-all coupling, deeper.** Fable found `defaultMode` anchors `hub-identity`. If we null the default, where does hub-identity live on a keyword hub? Is \"discovery-only\" fully worked out? Does sk-design's 6-way co-fire have analogues elsewhere?\n101: 11. **Historical & evidential.** Why were defaults added (bulk commits)? What would a real zero-signal traffic corpus look like, and is it worth building vs the archetype+fixture approach?\n102: 12. **Contrarian pass.** Argue the STRONGEST case AGAINST the run-1 verdict — where might keeping a named default actually be right? Steelman \"auto-default is fine.\"\n103: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergent-agenda -->\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\"\ndescription: \"Deep research into whether a parent hub's routerPolicy.defaultMode should point at a child mode at all, or default to null (defer to the parent to disambiguate/detect). Evaluates each of the five auto-defaulting hubs for whether its default is the genuine dominant case or a presumption, and proposes a principled fleet policy encoded in the create-skill canon + route-gold benchmark.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"default mode policy research\"\n  - \"should hubs default to null\"\n  - \"parent hub defaultMode design\"\n  - \"defer to parent vs default to child\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"research\"\n---\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n\n# Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\n\n---\n\n## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\"\ndescription: \"Deep research into whether a parent hub's routerPolicy.defaultMode should point at a child mode at all, or default to null (defer to the parent to disambiguate/detect). Evaluates each of the five auto-defaulting hubs for whether its default is the genuine dominant case or a presumption, and proposes a principled fleet policy encoded in the create-skill canon + route-gold benchmark.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"default mode policy research\"\n  - \"should hubs default to null\"\n  - \"parent hub defaultMode design\"\n  - \"defer to parent vs default to child\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"research\"\n---\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n\n# Feature Specification: Parent-Hub defaultMode Policy Research\n\n---\n\n## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n\nA parent hub is a pure router: its `SKILL.md` never handles a request itself, it only dispatches to a child mode (or defers). `routerPolicy.defaultMode` is the hub's documented fallback when the request scores weakly. Today five hubs point `defaultMode` at a specific child (`sk-prompt`→`prompt-improve`, `cli-external-orchestration`→`cli-opencode`, `system-deep-loop`→`research`, `mcp-tooling`→`mcp-chrome-devtools`, `sk-design`→`interface`) while two use `null` (`sk-doc` defers to disambiguation; `sk-code` resolves its mode by surface detection). The open question: is \"default to a child\" a sound default, or a presumption that silently commits to a possibly-wrong mode — and should some or all of the five flip to `null`?\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n\n`defaultMode = <child>` auto-commits the hub to one mode when nothing specific fires. That is good UX when one child is overwhelmingly the common case (asking would be annoying), but a latent failure when the request was actually about a different mode — the hub silently mis-routes instead of deferring. `defaultMode = null` avoids the mis-route (the parent disambiguates or detects) at the cost of more clarification prompts. There is no articulated fleet policy for which hubs should do which, and the choice is currently ad hoc.\n\n### Purpose\n\nDetermine the principled policy for `defaultMode` per tier and per hub, and how to encode it so new skills inherit the right default rather than copying a neighbour's.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:research-context -->\n## 3. RESEARCH CONTEXT\n\n### The core question\n\nShould a parent hub's `routerPolicy.defaultMode` point at a child mode, or should it be `null` (defer to the parent's own `SKILL.md` to disambiguate or detect)? When is each correct?\n\n### What to investigate (each iteration should advance these)\n\n1. **Semantics.** Is \"default to a child\" coherent given the parent is a pure router with no mode of its own? What does the deterministic router-replay actually do when nothing scores and `defaultMode` is set vs `null` (route to the default child, emit nothing, or defer)? Confirm against `router-replay.cjs` behaviour, not assumption.\n2. **Per-hub verdict.** For each of the five auto-defaulting hubs, is the named default the genuine dominant (~80%) case for a request that already routed to that skill, or a presumption? Evidence: the hub's own modes, its playbook scenarios, and what a mis-default would cost.\n   - `sk-prompt` → `prompt-improve` (vs the niche `prompt-models`)\n   - `cli-external-orchestration` → `cli-opencode` (vs `cli-claude-code`, `cli-codex`)\n   - `system-deep-loop` → `research` (vs review, ai-council, improvement lanes)\n   - `mcp-tooling` → `mcp-chrome-devtools` (vs 5 other unrelated transports)\n   - `sk-design` → `interface` (vs foundations, motion, audit, md-generator)\n3. **The two null models.** `sk-doc` (keyword-routed, no sensible default → defer) vs `sk-code` (detection-routed → no keyword default). Are these the reference patterns the five should be measured against?\n4. **Interaction with the route-gold gate.** Under `sameSet` intent matching, does a `defaultMode` fallback ever emit a mode that fails or masks a route-gold scenario? Should the benchmark assert defer-vs-default behaviour explicitly (a scenario whose gold is \"defer / disambiguate\")?\n5. **Encoding.** How should the chosen policy live in the `create-skill` canon (the `parent_skill_hub_router_template.json` + schema doc) so a new hub picks `defaultMode` deliberately rather than by imitation? What decision rule distinguishes \"default to the dominant child\" from \"null / defer\"?\n\n### Constraints / ground truth\n\n- The parent `SKILL.md` is a pure router; there is no \"parent mode.\" Do not propose a default that is the parent itself.\n- `AMBIGUITY_DELTA` is a hard-coded constant (1) in the benchmark replay; `routerPolicy.ambiguityDelta` in JSON is inert. Reason about defaulting within that scoring model.\n- Recommendations that change a shipped `defaultMode` are behaviour changes to live routing — treat each as a proposal with a stated tradeoff (fewer wrong auto-picks vs more disambiguation prompts), not an auto-applied fix.\n\n### Deliverable\n\n`research/research.md` with: a per-hub verdict table (keep default / flip to null, with the dominant-case evidence and the mis-default cost), the principled decision rule, the benchmark implication (should defer be a gold outcome), and the exact `create-skill` canon change to encode it.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:research-context -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 4. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- The `defaultMode` design question across the 7 parent hubs (5 default-to-child, 2 null).\n- The decision rule + its encoding in the create-skill canon and the route-gold benchmark.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Actually flipping any shipped `defaultMode` (that is a follow-on decision per hub).\n- Layer-0 advisor (skill selection) — this is about Layer-1 mode selection only.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergent-agenda -->\n## 5. DIVERGENT EXPLORATION AGENDA (Run 2 — 20 iterations, non-converge)\n\nRun 1 (4 iterations, in `run1-archive/`) reached a clear answer: keep sk-prompt, flip 4 to null; a null hub's fallback should load the routing helper (`smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`), not a child or filler. Run 2 must NOT re-derive this — it must **diverge, expand, and stress-test**. Each iteration should open NEW territory. Do not converge; treat any \"we already know this\" as a signal to push into an unexplored angle. Candidate divergent threads (extend beyond these):\n\n1. **The fallback-resource rule, stress-tested.** Does loading the mode-map actually help a live model route better, or just add tokens? Is there a case where a child hint beats the mode-map? What is the ideal *shape* of the routing-helper resource (full registry vs a compressed disambiguation card)?\n2. **Layer-0 ↔ Layer-1 interaction.** How does the advisor's skill selection interact with a hub that defers? Does a null hub push disambiguation cost up to Layer 0? Should the advisor pre-resolve more, so hubs never hit zero-signal?\n3. **Live-mode reality.** On a null hub, does a real model presented with the mode-map disambiguate cleanly, or freeze / pick arbitrarily? Design the experiment.\n4. **Migration & rollback.** Safe ordering of the 4 flips; regression surface; how to detect a bad flip; can the flips be shipped behind a benchmark gate?\n5. **The third archetype, fully specified.** Exact schema, validator rules, and the `defaultConfigured` rename ripple across replay, gold, dashboards, docs.\n6. **Cross-hub generalization.** Should ALL hubs converge on one archetype? When is detection-routed (sk-code) the better answer than defer-routed? Could sk-design be detection-routed?\n7. **Second-order effects.** Does removing defaults measurably raise disambiguation friction? What NEW anti-patterns could null + mode-map introduce (e.g. mode-map bloat, stale registries, over-deferring)?\n8. **Multi-dominant hubs & bundling.** What if a hub genuinely has 2 co-equal common modes? Ordered-bundle vs defer vs a ranked mode-map.\n9. **Edge cases & failure modes.** Empty mode-map, single-mode hubs, a mode-registry that drifts from hub-router, a hub whose \"default\" is contextual (cli's runtime-dependence — generalize it).\n10. **The catch-all coupling, deeper.** Fable found `defaultMode` anchors `hub-identity`. If we null the default, where does hub-identity live on a keyword hub? Is \"discovery-only\" fully worked out? Does sk-design's 6-way co-fire have analogues elsewhere?\n11. **Historical & evidential.** Why were defaults added (bulk commits)? What would a real zero-signal traffic corpus look like, and is it worth building vs the archetype+fixture approach?\n12. **Contrarian pass.** Argue the STRONGEST case AGAINST the run-1 verdict — where might keeping a named default actually be right? Steelman \"auto-default is fine.\"\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergent-agenda -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":103,"totalLines":103,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1784313642491,"end":1784313642495}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d5689de285fbdb2016a5a772a474881919821a3336e6d1a95"}},"id":"prt_f71617dcf001f1ZREobEiFDvIC","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f716149d70017KCEoYGjX8F9Pz"}}
