e 19: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, resolve `{artifact_dir}` and persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` (shape: `reviewTarget`, `reviewTargetType`, `reviewDimensions`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `stopPolicy`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `lineageMode`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n  Line 43:   executor: native  # one of: native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n\n  Line 44:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional, executor-specific (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 45:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n\n  Line 46:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional\n\n  Line 47:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional\n\n  Line 48:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional\n\n  Line 75: | `executor` | N | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default | `native` | N |\n\n  Line 76: | `executor_model` | N | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation | none | N |\n\n  Line 77: | `executor_config_dir` | N | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default | none | N |\n\n  Line 78: | `executor_reasoning` | N | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default | none | N |\n\n  Line 79: | `executor_service_tier` | N | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default | none | N |\n\n  Line 80: | `executor_timeout` | N | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default | `900` | N |\n\n  Line 83: | `fanout_executors` | N | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N |\n\n  Line 86: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Review fan-out uses strongest-restriction: any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL. Native and CLI fan-out lineages run under `fanout-run.cjs` in the capped pool so every lineage shares retries, artifact checks, and stop-policy validation. The native adapter calls the `deep/review` command with the internal `--fanout-lineage-artifact-dir` override; it must not dispatch the LEAF `@deep-review` agent or a pasted phase-running prompt as a full-loop sub-agent. When fan-out includes `cli-opencode`, that lineage is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode session with its own lineage directory and session id; this is the documented exception to the cli-opencode self-invocation guard. Single-executor `cli-opencode` remains cross-runtime only.\n\n  Line 119:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n\n  Line 120:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n\n  Line 121:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n\n  Line 122:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n\n  Line 123:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n\n  Line 124:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n\n  Line 127:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n\n  Line 128:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n\n  Line 129:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch\n\n  Line 133:    |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n\n  Line 134:    |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n\n  Line 137:    +-- Defaults: maxIterations=7, convergenceThreshold=0.10, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, stop_policy=`convergence`, lineage_mode=`auto`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n\n  Line 141:    - The generated `deep-review-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n\n  Line 144:    - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n\n  Line 145:    - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n\n  Line 146:    - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n\n  Line 147:    - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n\n  Line 148:    - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n\n  Line 149:    - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n\n  Line 153:    - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n\n  Line 154:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n  Line 164:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the target text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, ``, or `gpt-5.4`\n\n  Line 165:    - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n\n  Line 203:    - `\"review executor drift across CLIs, E, all, A, 7, 0.10, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n\n  Line 219:     - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n\n  Line 425: # Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n\n  Line 432:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n\n  Line 433:   --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --config-dir=~/.claude-account2 --label=claude \\\n\n  Line 438:   --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n\n  Line 439:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_review.body.md:\n  Line 36:     ├─ Do NOT dispatch the general agent through Task; it is not a loop executor.\n\n  Line 85: 2. Treat target text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--lineage-timeout-hours`, `--stop-policy`, `--spec-folder`, lifecycle flags (`--restart`, `--lineage-mode`), executor flags, fan-out flags, the internal `--fanout-lineage-artifact-dir`, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_model-benchmark_auto.yaml:\n  Line 100:     reducer: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 178:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 186:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 190:         description: \"Render the final dashboard via reduce-state and present benchmark trends and stop reason\"\n\n  Line 191:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_research.body.md:\n  Line 112: 2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--lineage-timeout-hours`, `--stop-policy`, `--dry-run`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n\n  Line 132: When `dry_run=true`, the confirm YAML emits `dry_run_halt` JSONL preview lines to terminal output instead of appending to the live state log, and halts before executor dispatch, persistent state mutation, reducer refresh, or child-lineage spawn. A fresh packet will stop at the first persistent state boundary; an existing packet can read current state and convergence signals, render the next prompt for preview, then stop before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_presentation.txt:\n  Line 39:   executor:\n\n  Line 42:     model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 44:     service_tier: \"\"  # optional, executor-specific\n\n  Line 70: | `executor.mode` | Y | flag `--executor-mode`, marker `executor.mode`, or default | `in-cli` | N |\n\n  Line 71: | `executor.cli` | Y | flag `--executor`, marker `executor.cli`, or active runtime | `active-runtime` | N |\n\n  Line 72: | `executor.model` | N | flag `--model`, marker `executor.model`, or executor default | none | N |\n\n  Line 73: | `executor.reasoning` | N | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor.reasoning`, or executor default | none | N |\n\n  Line 74: | `executor.service_tier` | N | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor.service_tier`, or executor default | none | N |\n\n  Line 75: | `executor.timeout` | N | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor.timeout`, or default | `900` | N |\n\n  Line 104:    |-- --executor-mode=<in-cli|external-cli> -> executor.mode\n\n  Line 105:    |-- --executor=<active-runtime|cli-opencode|cli-claude-code> -> executor.cli\n\n  Line 106:    |-- --model=<id> -> executor.model\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"phase_(main_loop|synthesis)|step_dispatch|step_synth|reduce-state|renderPrompt|executor","time":{"start":1784313655653,"end":1784313655681}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0217fc8d9cb088e6016a5a773774b88191a0dbe19a3dca4932"}},"id":"prt_f7161b100001kKyvOpn4j8hfzT","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f716181d8001gJ6bBGfabUBudq"}}
