{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313664476,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_BT31aqC88KF0KsQbNfqgn8dS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"step_dispatch|phase_synthesis|post_dispatch|reduce-state|renderPromptPack|cli-opencode","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 26:     cli: \"[active-runtime|cli-opencode|cli-claude-code|cli-opencode] - One CLI per round.\"\n\n  Line 148:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_skill-benchmark_presentation.txt:\n  Line 75: Mode A (router-replay) scores D1-intra, D2, D3, D5 deterministically. Mode B (live playbook) dispatches a skill's own `manual_testing_playbook` corpus through `cli-opencode`; it is advisory, and the gated verdict stays router mode plus the D5 hard gate.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_agent-improvement_auto.yaml:\n  Line 94:     reducer: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 249:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 261:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_presentation.txt:\n  Line 41:     cli: active-runtime  # active-runtime | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n\n  Line 42:     model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 105:    |-- --executor=<active-runtime|cli-opencode|cli-claude-code> -> executor.cli\n\n  Line 145:      B) cli-opencode - one external OpenCode round.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_agent-improvement_presentation.txt:\n  Line 460: - **Dispatcher**: `scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` is the model-agnostic dispatcher (executor routing across cli-opencode, cli-claude-code, cli-opencode). It loads only on the model-benchmark path, never in agent-improvement mode.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt:\n  Line 39:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n\n  Line 40:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 94:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n\n  Line 127:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n  Line 137:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n\n  Line 157:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--vari