{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314393545,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_QIOlD1PMzNC4Z40R44QqEHny","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/prompts/iteration-2.md\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+STATE SUMMARY: Iteration 2 of 3. One of five questions is answered. Last ratio 1.00. Stop policy is max-iterations; do not synthesize early. Iteration 1 established that replay default telemetry is not child selection and proposed a paired live experiment.\n+\n+Research Topic: Parent-hub defaultMode policy, run 2: a divergent multi-model deep dive over the Divergent Exploration Agenda in the packet spec.md.\n+Iteration: 2 of 3\n+Focus Area: Specify the paired live experiment as a runnable benchmark matrix: corpus construction, named-versus-null packet variants, blind grading rubric, sample design, falsification thresholds per hub, and full-registry versus compressed-card fallback resources.\n+Remaining Key Questions: live behavior and fallback evaluation; migration/schema safety; cross-hub edge cases; second-order anti-patterns\n+Carried-Forward Open Questions: read strategy and registry\n+Last 3 Iterations Summary: run 1 contrarian and live-routing pass (1.00)\n+Pivot Lineage: from deterministic semantics to empirical live-routing design\n+Saturated Directions: re-deriving run 1; equating defaultApplied with selection; replay-only conclusions\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc