/research/lineages/sol-ultra/prompts/iteration-3.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/prompts/iteration-3.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/prompts/iteration-3.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,45 @@\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+STATE SUMMARY: Iteration 3 of 3. Two of five questions are answered. Ratios 1.00 -> 0.90. This is the mandatory final evidence iteration under max-iterations, not synthesis. Prior passes resolved deterministic semantics and designed a factorial live benchmark.\n+\n+Research Topic: Parent-hub defaultMode policy, run 2: a divergent multi-model deep dive over the Divergent Exploration Agenda in the packet spec.md.\n+Iteration: 3 of 3\n+Focus Area: Specify migration and schema safety for a third archetype: exact field semantics, validator changes, `defaultApplied` rename ripple, rollout order, rollback telemetry, and cross-hub edge cases including contextual and multi-dominant defaults.\n+Remaining Key Questions: third-archetype safety; binary-policy edge cases; second-order anti-patterns\n+Carried-Forward Open Questions: read strategy and registry\n+Last 3 Iterations Summary: run 1 contrarian semantics (1.00); run 2 runnable benchmark matrix (0.90)\n+Pivot Lineage: semantics -> empirical design -> migration/schema and edge-case stress test\n+Saturated Directions: run-1 verdict re-derivation; replay-only conclusions; confounded two-arm tests\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/findings-registry.json\n+- Write iteration narrative to: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+- Write per-iteration delta to: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- Execute exactly one LEAF research iteration. Do not dispatch sub-agents and do not synthesize research.md.\n+- Read state and both prior iterations first. Open a new territory rather than repeating their conclusions.\n+- Perform 3-5 focused repository research actions on schemas, validators, replay telemetry consumers, docs, tests, and hub edge cases.\n+- Write only iteration-003.md, append exactly one iteration-3 state record, and create iter-003.jsonl.\n+- Do not modify researched source, config, strategy, registry, dashboard, or any path outside the three allowed targets.\n+- BANNED OPERATIONS: rm, mv, git rm, rmdir, sed -i, truncating unrelated files, or any out-of-scope write.\n+- Every finding needs repository citations or explicit inference.\n+- Route proof MUST be exactly `target_agent:\"deep-research\"` without `@`, and `resolved_route:\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"` without semicolons or extra text.\n+- Include complete canonical iteration fields with `iteration:3` and `run:3`; delta first line must exactly match the appended object.\n+\n+## RESEARCH EMPHASIS\n+\n+- Distinguish selection policy from recommendation metadata in the schema.\n+- Trace the actual `defaultApplied` and `defaultConfigured` terminology surface and identify migration compatibility needs.\n+- Design safe sequencing, rollback signals, and benchmark gates without proposing immediate live flips.\n+- Stress contextual defaults, multi-dominant hubs, empty/single-mode maps, stale registries, detection-routed hubs, and new null-induced anti-patterns.\n","additions":45,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/prompts/iteration-3.md","time":{"start":1784315089166,"end":1784315089168}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03567e42cd516946016a5a7cad3ba88191bf11f17562940d72"}},"id":"prt_f717704cb001WA78Q6RJcAPA33","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f7176ebd0001szlD1xfZSJUI7Z"}}
