{"type":"text","timestamp":1784315531534,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"id":"prt_f717e2e7d001TaCbadcNMblH3P","messageID":"msg_f717df5c1001rS7akVkY03uBGu","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","type":"text","text":"All three leaf iterations now pass the canonical narrative, route-proof, and delta gate. The final pass produced the additive three-archetype schema and migration safety model; I’m consolidating the three evidence streams into the lineage synthesis, resource map, terminal state, and dashboard.","time":{"start":1784315522685,"end":1784315531533},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_072cc8b6be191dda016a5a7e826fb08191895305d7c6c2eab8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784315531766,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8WHoeAlxSSudxqNEcgIbrK5G","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/findings-registry.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [\n3:     \"What exact third-archetype schema, migration order, rollback telemetry, and benchmark contracts would make policy changes safe?\",\n4:     \"Which cross-hub edge cases break a binary named-default-versus-null policy?\",\n5:     \"What second-order anti-patterns emerge from null routing, mode-map loading, contextual defaults, or multi-dominant modes?\"\n6:   ],\n7:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n8:     \"What is the strongest evidence-backed case that named defaults remain preferable, and where does the run-1 verdict overreach?\",\n9:     \"How should named-versus-null policy and fallback-resource shape be evaluated in a runnable live benchmark without mutating shipped hubs?\"\n10:   ],\n11:   \"keyFindings\": [\n12:     \"Zero-signal replay leaves workflowMode null while defaultApplied reports only that a named default is configured.\",\n13:     \"sk-prompt supports a bounded named recommendation, but repository fixtures do not prove an 80 percent traffic share.\",\n14:     \"CLI and MCP gold scenarios explicitly require defer despite configured named defaults.\",\n15:     \"A paired live named-versus-null benchmark is needed to distinguish harmless metadata from behavior-shaping bias.\",\n16:     \"A 2x4 policy-by-helper fixture matrix isolates named-versus-null behavior from fallback-resource shape.\",\n17:     \"A balanced ambiguity corpus, blind evidence grading, and repeated blocked sampling make live results auditable.\",\n18:     \"Full registry, compressed card, child hint, and no-helper arms test distinct routing and token-cost hypotheses.\"\n19:   ],\n20:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n21:     \"Treating routeTelemetry.defaultApplied as evidence that replay selected the default child.\",\n22:     \"Using deterministic replay alone to settle live-model behavior.\",\n23:     \"A simple named-versus-null A/B test with one shared helper.\",\n24:     \"Treating the full registry as the automatic control winner.\",\n25:     \"Using one live run per case.\"\n26:   ],\n27:   \"metrics\": {\n28:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n29:     \"openQuestions\": 3,\n30:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n31:     \"keyFindings\": 7,\n32:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.95,\n33:     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n34:   },\n35:   \"divergence\": {\n36:     \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n37:     \"completed\": [],\n38:     \"failures\": [],\n39:     \"overrides\": []\n40:   }\n41: }\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What exact third-archetype schema, migration order, rollback telemetry, and benchmark contracts would make policy changes safe?\",\n    \"Which cross-hub edge cases break a binary named-default-versus-null policy?\",\n    \"What second-order anti-patterns emerge from null routing, mode-map loading, contextual defaults, or multi-dominant modes?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What is the strongest evidence-backed case that named defaults remain preferable, and where does the run-1 verdict overreach?\",\n    \"How should named-versus-null policy and fallback-resource shape be evaluated in a runnable live benchmark without mutating shipped hubs?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    \"Zero-signal replay leaves workflowMode null while defaultApplied reports only that a named default is configured.\",\n    \"sk-prompt supports a bounded named recommendation, but repository fixtures do not prove an 80 percent traffic share.\",\n    \"CLI and MCP gold scenarios explicitly require defer despite configured named defaults.\",\n    \"A paired live named-versus-null benchmark is needed to distinguish harmless metadata from behavior-shaping bias.\",\n    \"A 2x4 policy-by-helper fixture matrix isolates named-versus-null behavior from fallback-resource shape.\",\n    \"A balanced ambiguity corpus, blind evidence grading, and repeated blocked sampling make live results auditable.\",\n    \"Full registry, compressed card, child hint, and no-helper arms test distinct routing and token-cost hypotheses.\"\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What exact third-archetype schema, migration order, rollback telemetry, and benchmark contracts would make policy changes safe?\",\n    \"Which cross-hub edge cases break a binary named-default-versus-null policy?\",\n    \"What second-order anti-patterns emerge from null routing, mode-map loading, contextual defaults, or multi-dominant modes?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What is the strongest evidence-backed case that named defaults remain preferable, and where does the run-1 verdict overreach?\",\n    \"How should named-versus-null policy and fallback-resource shape be evaluated in a runnable live benchmark without mutating shipped hubs?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    \"Zero-signal replay leaves workflowMode null while defaultApplied reports only that a named default is configured.\",\n    \"sk-prompt supports a bounded named recommendation, but repository fixtures do not prove an 80 percent traffic share.\",\n    \"CLI and MCP gold scenarios explicitly require defer despite configured named defaults.\",\n    \"A paired live named-versus-null benchmark is needed to distinguish harmless metadata from behavior-shaping bias.\",\n    \"A 2x4 policy-by-helper fixture matrix isolates named-versus-null behavior from fallback-resource shape.\",\n    \"A balanced ambiguity corpus, blind evidence grading, and repeated blocked sampling make live results auditable.\",\n    \"Full registry, compressed card, child hint, and no-helper arms test distinct routing and token-cost hypotheses.\"\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    \"Treating routeTelemetry.defaultApplied as evidence that replay selected the default child.\",\n    \"Using deterministic replay alone to settle live-model behavior.\",\n    \"A simple named-versus-null A/B test with one shared helper.\",\n    \"Treating the full registry as the automatic control winner.\",\n    \"Using one live run per case.\"\n  ],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n    \"keyFindings\": 7,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.95,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n  },\n  \"divergence\": {\n    \"saturatedDirections\": [],\n    \"completed\": [],\n    \"failures\": [],\n    \"overrides\": []\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784315531761,"end":1784315531765}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072cc8b6be191dda016a5a7e8b768481919ce56b6576c1151b"}},"id":"prt_f717e512e00157mw8X34tnlIob","sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","messageID":"msg_f717df5c1001rS7akVkY03uBGu"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784315531833,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082c9ffe7l0Exu0UkBOne2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gO9HHi5I8rGmJCblnkXVHWs8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard: sol-ultra\n2: \n3: ## Lifecycle\n4: \n5: - Session: `fanout-sol-ultra-1784313510669-wn3vsj`\n6: - Generation: 1\n7: - Status: iterating\n8: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n9: \n10: ## Iterations\n11: \n12: | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n13: |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n14: | 1 | Contrarian and live-routing pass | 1.00 | 4 | complete |\n15: | 2 | Runnable live-routing benchmark matrix | 0.90 | 6 | complete |\n16: \n17: ## Question Status\n18: \n19: - Answered: 2 / 5\n20: - Remaining: 3\n21: \n22: ## Convergence Trend\n23: \n24: - Ratios: 1.00 -> 0.90\n25: - Convergence is telemetry only until iteration 3.\n26: \n27: ## Dead Ends\n28: \n29: - `defaultApplied` is not evidence of actual child selection.\n30: - Deterministic replay alone cannot settle live-model behavior.\n31: - A two-arm test confounds policy with helper-resource shape.\n32: - Single-sample live verdicts are below the repository stability floor.\n33: \n34: ## Next Focus\n35: \n36: Specify the third-archetype schema, migration and rollback contract, validator ripple, and cross-hub edge cases.\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard: sol-ultra\n\n## Lifecycle\n\n- Session: `fanout-sol-ultra-1784313510669-wn3vsj`\n- Generation: 1\n- Status: iterating\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n\n## Iterations\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Contrarian and live-routing pass | 1.00 | 4 | complete |\n| 2 | Runnable live-routing benchmark matrix | 0.90 | 6 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 2 / 5\n- Remaining: 3","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard: sol-ultra\n\n## Lifecycle\n\n- Session: `fanout-sol-ultra-1784313510669-wn3vsj`\n- Generation: 1\n- Status: iterating\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n\n## Iterations\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Contrarian and live-routing pass | 1.00 | 4 | complete |\n| 2 | Runnable live-routing benchmark matrix | 0.90 | 6 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 2 / 5\n- Remaining: 3\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 1.00 -> 0.90\n- Convergence is telemetry only until iteration 3.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- `defaultApplied` is not evidence of actual child selection.\n- Deterministic replay alone cannot settle live-model behavior.\n- A two-arm test confounds policy with helper-resource shape.\n- Single-sample live verdicts are below the repository stability floor.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nSpecify the third-archetype schema, migration and rollback contract, validator ripple, and cross-hub edge cases.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":36,"totalLines":36,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/sol-ultra/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784315531829,"end":1784315531832}},"metadata":{"ope